import React,{useState} from "react" import './App.css'; import { useHistory } from "react-router-dom" function AddAnimal({AddAnimal}){ const navigate = useHistory() const [name, setName] = useState("") function handleSubmit(e){ e.preventDefault() const newAnimal = { name:name, breed:breed, age:age, gender:gender, size:size, weight:weight, personality:personality, healthStatus:healthStatus, AvailabilityStatus:AvailabilityStatus, image:image, } fetch("http://localhost:3000/animals",{ method:"POST", headers: { "Content-Type":"application/json", }, body: JSON.stringify(newAnimal) }) .then((response)=>response.json()) .then((data) => AddAnimal(data)) setInputClear() Navigate('/'); } function setInputClear(){ setName() setBreed() setAge("") setGender("") setSize("") setWeight("") setPersonality("") SetHealthStatus("") setAvailabilityStatus("") image("") } return( // display the form with input fields and a submit button
